Objective: Test the SSL/TLS configuration of a website using Kali Linux tools
Tools used: nmap, OpenSSL, and SSLscan

SSL SCAN
Command: sslscan --show-certificate google.com
Output Explanation:
TLS FALLBACK SCSV: server supports TLS fallback scsv (This means it is protecting the TLS from downgrade attacks)
TLS renegotiation: secure session renegotiation supported (Ensures proper authentication and verification during renegotiation)

NMAP SCAN
Command: nmap --script ssl-enum-ciphers -p 443 google.com
Output Explanation: listing of TLSv1.0, TLSv1.1, TLSv1.2, and TLSv1.3 shows the TLS versions that the server supports.

OPENSSL SCAN
Command: openssl s_client -connect google.com:443
Output: certificate chain
